      • seatParty

        public java.lang.String seatParty()
        Attempts to seat the first party to have arrived that is still waiting to be seated. Only seats parties at tables big enough to hold them in their entirety.
        Returns:
        a String containing data about the parties that were not seated, and the one that was (if there is one).

      • partyExits

        public java.lang.String partyExits(java.lang.String name)
        The restaurant exits the party with the given name and frees the table they're at, if they exist.
        Parameters:
        name - the name of the party.
        Returns:
        a string containing information about the party who exited, if it exists, or null otherwise.

      • addTable

        public void addTable(Table table,
                     boolean petSection)
        Adds a table into the given section. Precondition: No table already exists with the given name in the specified section.
        Parameters:
        table - the Table to be added
        petSection - true if this table goes in the Pet section, false otherwise.

      • removeTable

        public java.lang.String removeTable(java.lang.String name,
                                    boolean petSection)
        Removes a table with the specified name from the specified section, if it exists and is possible. Will not remove a table that is currently in-use or one that is in the wrong section.
        Parameters:
        name - the name of the table to remove.
        petSection - true if the table should be removed from the pet section, false otherwise.
        Returns:
        a string with information regarding the table's removal.

      • partyNameFree

        public boolean partyNameFree(java.lang.String name)
        Checks whether a party with a given name exists in the restaurant.
        Parameters:
        name - the name to search for
        Returns:
        true if a party waiting or seated has the given name, false otherwise.

      • tableNameFree

        public boolean tableNameFree(java.lang.String name,
                             boolean petSection)
        Checks whether a table with the specified name can be placed in the section preferred.
        Parameters:
        name - the name to check.
        petSection - true if searching in the pets-allowed, false otherwise.
        Returns:
        true if the name is free, false otherwise.
